  "term": "thm:supremum-difference-set",
  "kind": "Theorem",
  "title": "Supremum of a Difference Set",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $A,B\\subseteq\\mathbb{R}$ be nonempty, with $A$ bounded above and $B$ bounded below. Then\n\\[\n \\sup(A-B)=\\sup A-\\inf B,\n \\qquad\n A-B=\\{a-b:a\\in A,\\ b\\in B\\}.\n\\]",
